A bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look at the interiors of Gaudi
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric lizard, the stairs like the spine of a dinosaur, and the balconies are ripped fish columns.
This is the Casa Batlló by the Catalan architect Antonio Gaudi in Barcelona.
From the local inhabitants, the house with its organic forms was nicknamed "bone house".
Organic shapes, wild colors, the unusual use of stone, tile fragments and mosaics, the scale-like facades and ubiquitous soft lines, all these are typical features of Antonio Gaudi’s Art Nouveau style.
The fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade of the house plays with dreamy lines, tender colors and textures, reminiscent of nature and living beings.
Only with a closer look can you see that everything is dominated by geometry, rhythm and thoughtful order.
At night, the entire fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade looks even more plastic, dramatic and the special illumination reinforces the shine of the colors.
The same vivid lines and convoluted shapes also dominate the interior of the house.
Wave-shaped wood copies the window frames, railings, decorative elements of doors, even look holes and strips.
The house Batlló in the Eixample district on the bustling shopping street Passeig de Grácia No. 43 was built by the architect Emilio Sala Cortese in 1877.
The reconstruction took two years and was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialist Josep Batlló, originally insisted on the demolition of the old and the construction of a completely new building, but ultimately he agreed with Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s idea of an unusual and also cheaper reconstruction.
However, the Casa Batlló rental house did not design Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> alone.
He worked with the architect Josep Maria Jujol.
It was precisely on his drawing board that the decorations for the representative apartment of the reality owner were created and also the use of mosaics on the facade was his idea.
However, numerous other sculptors and artists also collaborated on the design of the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade.
The joint work on the designs for Casa Batlló was the beginning of a fruitful collaboration between Jujola and Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Jujol also participated in the construction of Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s Casa Milá house in Park Güell, which also houses other works by Antoni Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>.
Shortly after its completion, the house was given by the local inhabitants of its organic forms because of the nickname "bone house".
Others in turn called it the special window opening mechanism because of the "grooming house".
It is also said that at the top of the building is depicted the sword of St. George, the patron saint of Catalonia.
But other sculptural elements also symbolize hidden religious motifs.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> designed for the house a central heating system with vents and typical fireplaces unique for the time.
Something bizarre about her 45-degree inclination.
In his work, Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> consistently ignored all the building regulations of the time and did not allow himself to be fooled by them.
Before construction began, he obtained the corresponding building permit from the city, but the information he gave about the planned reconstruction was so vague that the city fathers were so horrified at the result two years later when it was completed that they demanded relief.
Among other things, the councillors met with the fact that the building with its pillars even intervened in the public sidewalk.
However, there were no more changes, quite the contrary - only fifteen days after the request of the district, Josep Batlló made a request to approve the rental of the two highest floors of the house - and it was promptly granted to him.
The homeowner himself moved into the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor was a social salon, on the third floor were the bedrooms and private rooms of the apartment.
The ground floor was leased to a jewellery store.
The entire six-storey building runs through a staircase up to the roof terrace.
The basic elements of the conversion eliminated all right angles and straight lines and replaced them with curved and curved walls.
But Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked with a modern concept for the mutual connection of spaces.
The social part can be completely connected by opening the salon doors and thus a larger society could chat comfortably without having to give up a certain intimacy in more confidential conversations.
In addition to a new fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade, the house received a rather unusual roof and two other floors due to Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s reconstruction.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD>’s play with the light as well as the blue and white glazed tiles, with which the courtyard and the courtyards are covered, is also impressive.
The play of these two colors gives all floors of the house a maximum of light.
In doing so, he simply used the principle that white reflects light better than dark colors, which absorb sunlight on the contrary.
The Casa Batlló, which was added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in 2005, can now be visited by anyone.
On the first floor, the most spacious and magnificent apartment is made accessible to the public.
The homeowners only decided in the year to this step and this on the occasion of the 150th birthday of the famous creator.
When it was determined that this was a fairly profitable business, the visits were kept, and they were also extended to other common rooms and the attic, including the roof terrace.
However, the price for visiting the monument is not a cardboard stick, it is 16.50 euros, students, retirees, groups and holders of tourist cards receive 20 percent discount.
This amount exceeds the entrance fees to other Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> buildings in the city.
If you want to get to know the real atmosphere of the house with its dragon towers, try to make friends with one of the house dwellers and visit him at home.
The right mattress and the right bed grate? Women have different desires than men
Not the best bed frame, but the quality of the lying area - so mattress and rust make up the good bed.
However, these must be complemented harmoniously in order to meet the wishes of the specific user.
In the selection, many things play a role - the weight, the size, the state of health and, last but not least, the sex of the sleeper.
Equally important is the interior, in which mattress and rust have to be subordinated.
Typical example?
In a weekend house where it is not heated regularly, latex mattresses are not well suited, as they take much longer to "get warm".
In addition, they are significantly heavier than conventional polyurethane mattresses.
And - they should be turned regularly.
If they do not have enough venting channels in the core and also lie on a solid plate, moisture builds up: it is therefore not excluded that mold forms under their mold.
Of course, the choice also plays a role in what you are accustomed to.
Those who have been abroad for a long time, where very high mattresses with a soft layer are common, will find it difficult to get used to a low mattress with a hard surface.
“All the ice hockey players who have returned from the NHL have complained to me that they can’t sleep here properly anymore.”
"For their skinned shoulders, heels and hips, they simply need a soft layer of visco foam (Memory Foam - a shape memory polymer)."
“I recommend these, among other things, to sugar-sick people who suffer from a disorder of the nervous system, so that they can receive the “information” from the joints and the skin poorly,” explains Sylva Hadamcziková, who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That’s why I bought these mattresses with Visco foam (Memory Foam) for many ice hockey players years ago, but also for other customers.
"Today this is no longer a problem, because such mattresses offer, among others, the manufacturer Tempur, the Italian company Magniflex or the Czech manufacturer Tropico."
And you don’t necessarily have to be a famous ice hockey player to appreciate the benefits of visco foam.
This "miracle" actually works quite simply.
The foam optimizes its hardness and shape according to the absorbed heat, in other words, it really clings to the warm body.
Nowhere does it press, in the night you do not roll around like after a heavy fight.
You just sleep a lot better.
The viscoelastic foam also offers protection against decubitus (burn).
When choosing the size of the mattress, you should still add the length of the soles of the feet, i.e. about 21 to 34 cm.
Both men and women, who are 180 cm tall, need such a 210 to 220 cm long bed.
Each of the sleepers should have at least 90 cm of lying width available, i.e. together 180 cm.
For single beds, for example, singles, 120 to 140 cm are fitted.
For the sake of comfort and also for eventual visitors.
Otherwise, the following rule of thumb applies for the ideal bed width: "If you lie on your back, there should be enough room for the slightly bent arms," advises Ing. Helena Prokopová, the guild master of upholsterers and room decorators, who has been devoting herself to the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture school for years and also focuses on this subject.
With a double bed, everyone needs their own grate and their own mattress, but be careful when shopping so that the mattresses are the same height.
Otherwise, there is no other option than to mount the grate at different heights and this is not possible with every bed frame.
Foam mattresses should be at least 14 cm high, mattresses with feather skeleton 15 cm, of which at least three centimeters should be on the mold layer and the fine cushion.
"With your hand or when sitting down, you must not feel the feathers," warns Helena Prokopová.
Each mattress requires a special type of rust.
Upholstered beds with mattress and mattress, such as siamese twins, have nothing to look for in the bedroom.
These mattresses cannot be ventilated and the cover cannot be washed, which is already common today.
And since you lose between 0.2 and 0.75 l of sweat in a single night, it is clear that the mattress will slowly become a huge (and clogged) sieve after five to seven years.
This is also why professionals reject advertising slogans that promise a lifetime of up to 25 years for mattresses, even a lifetime guarantee.
Every thing has its if and but.
And therefore a practical advice from the dealers: With mattresses of 120 or 140 cm width, one should not shy away from the hygiene of the washable, removable covers, however, it is recommended to use a mattress protector, which can be easily removed and washed.
Even though mattress covers are usually made with a round zipper, so that you get two halves after opening (immensely important for the washing process and the size of the washing machine!), the manipulation with larger mattresses, especially performed alone, often looks like the unequal fight between David and Goliath.
Do they have a fixed plate in bed instead of a grate?
Get out of here!
Or at most for a bed for unloved guests and for a single night.
Also, they should prefer to use the plate with ventilation holes (if they are not already inside) and mattresses with spring skeleton and 15 cm minimum height with so-called pocket spring core and fine padding.
Polyurethane mattresses do not belong on such a base.
Latex or sandwich mattresses (also combinations of latex and coconut) are suitable for non-adjustable lattice bars with 14 to 18 spring strips (lamellae), always with a larger number of lattice bars, i.e. of 28 and more spring strips, with lattice support in the lumbar region and the possibility of regulating the hardness of the lattice.
Mattresses with a spring skeleton do not belong to adjustable lamellar grids, as they do not respond to the ergonomic adjustment.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the spring strips, special flexible shoulder modules are also offered.
This involves a special fastening of the spring strips, which makes it possible to press in the spring strips or even to bend them in such a way that they allow the shoulder of the sleeper to sink punctually.
Especially for men with wide shoulders an important thing.
There are even mattress manufacturers who have started using soft zones for the shoulder area in "man's mattresses".
The ladies are also thought of - they are granted these soft zones in the hip area.
For the most demanding customers, point-elastic wing spring systems (Lattoflex) or grate with point-elastic contact pads with so-called multi-torsion suspension are designed.
The pressure is distributed over several points, which reduces the tension.
But - if you use a bad (too large and full) pillow for the right mattress and rust, most of the benefits are lost again.
Here, too, a rule of thumb: the pillow should support the head, its tips should only reach up to the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can relax.
Ideally, therefore, a pillow of 50 x 60 cm will appear, as the Scandinavians like, for example.
In the side position, the pillow (together with the shoulder relief zone in the grate or the soft zone in the mattress) should balance the shoulder height.
Our modern mattresses have something in common with the old straw bags (filled with hay).
Modern manufacturers increasingly use natural materials or at least their admixtures.
Also for mattresses, the new magic word is "organic".
Instead of petroleum raw materials, natural oils are increasingly used for the production of polyurethane foams - for example castor and soybean oil.
Soy is probably used by all known manufacturers.
"In mattresses, organic is their core made of materials of pure natural origin," explains Petr Va<0xC5><0xA1><0xC3><0xAD><0xC4><0x8D>ek from Tropico Plus.
Natural substances are also used in the production of mattress covers - one of the first was aloe vera.
However, you can also indulge in microcapsules that spread fresh forest or lavender scent while sleeping.
Again, there is a difference between a man and a woman.
While men use a "cooling" plant extract from birch leaves to allow the mattress cover to absorb heat and cool the body, the covers have a "warming" effect for women.
Extracts from red peppers stimulate blood circulation, so the weaker sex gets pleasantly warm during sleep.
What about today’s favorites?
Cold foam mattresses (it has larger pores with destroyed cell structure and is therefore more breathable than commercial polyurethane and also much more flexible).
By combining the various stiffnesses (hardness) of cold foams and visco foams, multi-zone mattresses are created that know exactly where the head, hips and heels are.
For a high-quality mattress, however, you have to pay 7,000 crowns and more.
However, health mattresses are usually charged with lower VAT since they are considered medical aids.
Gumotex was the first Czech company to achieve this advantage.
You can see that saving on the mattress and the rust is not so easy.
From time to time, there are special offers from manufacturers and dealers who offer two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, the Magniflex brand offers the Duofreeze mattress with covered Visco foam memory for 11,990 CZK.
The second one is free of charge.
It was the material Tempur that ushered in the era of viscoelastic foams with open cell structure and high density at an almost cosmic pace.
No wonder they were developed for NASA, because the astronauts are exposed to enormous overloads at the launches.
