Last year, when information about this affair first came to the public, Mr. Ensign apologized to his constituents and resigned his position in the Senate, where he had ranked fourth in the Republican rankings.
After failing to notice for many months, Mr. Ensign told reporters two weeks ago that he was seeking a third term in the Senate.
In announcing that Mr. Ensign would no longer be the target of police investigations, his press spokeswoman, Jennifer Cooper, the senator, said he hoped the ethics commission would very quickly follow the example of the Justice Department and stop its investigations.
“Senator Ensign is looking forward to continuing his hard work serving the people of Nevada,” she said.
